<item>
            <title>[LU-11467] FLR1.5: add &quot;lfs mirror delete&quot; command</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11467</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror split --destroy&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; is not a very obvious way to remove mirrors from a file.  It would be useful to add &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror delete&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (with a man page, of course) to do the same thing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror split&lt;/tt&gt; command currently requires specifying an explicit mirror ID, but it would be more useful to allow &lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror delete&lt;/tt&gt; to directly use &lt;tt&gt;lfs getstripe&lt;/tt&gt; options like &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;comp&amp;#45;flags=prefer&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;&amp;#45;&amp;#45;pool=flash&lt;/tt&gt; to remove replicas.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="53488">LU-11467</key>
